      "writtenOn": "2026-04-27T10:51:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you use function pointer / per-platform lookup tables then it is already decoupled.\n\n\nThe problem with decoupling it with systemd targets is that it prevents people from refactoring this design or implementation in the future.\n\nSince you provide extension points via systemd which can then be used by downstream code or platform maintainers.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 63,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 65,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "d54bfcb4b068b0c7ef04e1a0a72b525bcd7b91f3",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
