        "id": 1002134
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-07T11:24:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just to confirm my understanding: with a function-pointer / lookup-table approach, would platform-specific hardware operations (GPIO, I2C, etc.) need to be compiled into the state manager binary, or would some other mechanism be used to keep them separate?\n\nThe current PSM pattern uses systemd targets to keep hardware-specific code out of the state daemon entirely. I followed the same approach here.\n@geissonator@yahoo.com, could you share your thoughts on whether a different extension mechanism is preferred for sub-devices?",
      "parentUuid": "a9e68b83_58616ca6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 63,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 65,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "d54bfcb4b068b0c7ef04e1a0a72b525bcd7b91f3",
