      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-27T10:51:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So platforms need to do their own service wiring to get a sane default behavior?\n\nThis reminds me of the `rsyslog` story where each platform was copy-pasting the same configuration to get Redfish EventLog to work.\n\n\nIs it possible to instead inline that behavior into the code directly or configure it via EM?\n\n\nWhy do we need this infinite flexibility on the platform side to start whichever services when it\u0027s only 2 cases here. Either the drives power off with the host, or they do not. Is there other cases?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 189,
        "startChar": 62,
        "endLine": 190,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "d54bfcb4b068b0c7ef04e1a0a72b525bcd7b91f3",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "daa61bfe_eeaeecc2",
        "filename": "designs/sub-device-state-manager.md",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 190,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002134
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-07T11:24:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you for the concrete example with rsyslog.\n\nI think for the common case (drives power off with host), the daemon could handle this internally: observe CurrentHostState for the associated host and initiate poweroff for drives with matching `ManagedHost` when the host goes off. That way platforms would not need any systemd wiring for host-drive power dependency.\n\nPlatform-specific target hooks would still be needed for the actual hardware power control (GPIO, I2C), since that varies per platform.\n\nI will update the doc to propose this approach and clarify the distinction.",
      "parentUuid": "26caa346_f6260ee8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 189,
        "startChar": 62,
        "endLine": 190,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "d54bfcb4b068b0c7ef04e1a0a72b525bcd7b91f3",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
