      },
      "lineNbr": 318,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001712
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-27T10:51:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The host power state tracking is also replicated. The linux per process overhead is also replicated. The overall binary size increases since `-Osize` does not work properly  due to duplicated codes.\n\nThe overhead of system services and associated metadata tracking is also duplicated. There is also additional logs generated from service startup.\n\n\nOne of my use-cases is to be able to emulate things in qemu.\n\nWhile per-instance and per-type designs may run okay on a real hardware, they are significantly less efficient than single-binary single-process designs.\n\nSince lots of developers rely on qemu, i would be happy if we could prioritize optimal solutions in regards to memory use, binary size and runtime overhead.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 316,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 318,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "d54bfcb4b068b0c7ef04e1a0a72b525bcd7b91f3",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9d1bba6_d555e0af",
        "filename": "designs/sub-device-state-manager.md",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 318,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002134
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-07T11:24:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you for the detailed review and feedback.\n\nThe sub-device daemons are expected to be much smaller than bmcweb, and each new device type would add incrementally (the shared infrastructure is built once, per-type code is minimal). That said, I understand the efficiency argument for a consolidated approach, and a single binary with type selection is feasible.\n\nMy starting point was the existing per-type binary convention in PSM and dbus-sensors, with the practical benefit of recipe-level inclusion/exclusion. But I am open to either direction.\n\n@patrick@stwcx.xyz @geissonator@yahoo.com do you have a preference between per-type binaries vs a single combined sub-device\nbinary? Happy to implement whichever you prefer.",
      "parentUuid": "450307b7_c1af52ac",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 316,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 318,
        "endChar": 62
      },
